    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-08-26T12:13:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-08-26T12:13:00-05:00" n="874"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d874">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">784A.5/8–2254: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 874<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Embassy in Israel</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-08-26T13:13:00-04:00"
                            >August 26, 1954—1:13 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>109. <gloss target="#t_urtel1">Urtel</gloss> 190.<note n="1" xml:id="d874fn1">
                        <ref target="#d868">Document 868</ref>.</note> Department concurs fully with
                    line you took with <persName corresp="#p_EAS1">Eban</persName>. If suitable
                    opportunity arises you may wish express <persName corresp="#p_EAS1"
                        >Eban</persName> Department’s disappointment that his reaction to lengthy
                    exchanges views with Secretary and others has not been more constructive.
                    General tenor <persName corresp="#p_EAS1">Eban</persName>’s “four-point policy”
                    appears tantamount to recommendation Israel Government take little heed of
                    United States advice regarding timing and tactics toward our common objectives
                    of peace and stability in Near East. . . . <persName corresp="#p_EAS1"
                        >Eban</persName> plays such important role in conveying thinking this
                    government to his own, that it is hoped he would wish impress upon <gloss
                        target="#t_IG1">IG</gloss> sincerity Secretary’s assurances and depth of
                    support that lies behind them in America’s general desire for security and peace
                    for and <pb facs="1670" n="1630" xml:id="pg_1630"/> within area. America’s
                    security is deeply involved [as] well as Israel’s. It would be disappointment
                    American people if Israel were to continue in its endeavors block our attempts
                    encourage certain Near East leaders who are seeking identify their peoples’
                    destiny with that of Free World.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SRA1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Smith</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
